HEADWORD: Dr.
<hw>Dr.</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>abbreviation for
<altname>doctor</altname>, a title accorded to a person who holds a
doctorate degree from an academic institution, such as a Ph.D. degree or
M.D. degree.</def> <mark>[abbrev.]</mark> ⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> doctor.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a licensed doctor of medicine.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> doctor, doc, physician, MD, medico.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

